did.unittitle: University Photography Photograph Collection
did.abstract: This collection contains photographs taken by University Photography photographers of Tufts University events starting in 2005.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into two series. Within the first series files are organized by photoshoot. Some photoshoots are empty as further processing of files occurs. The second series contains unprocessed accessions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains photographs taken by University Photography photographers of Tufts University events starting in 2005. Events include matriculation, commencement, partents weekend, reunion, and special honorary events. The collection also includes stock photos of the Tufts campus.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproductions and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish. Copyright to all materials created by Tufts University employees in the course of their work is held by the Trustees of Tufts University.

did.unittitle: Photographs

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains photographs taken by University Photography photographers of Tufts University events starting in 2005.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is arranged by University Photography job number and photographer.

did.unittitle: Job 051016 SLE Puppets
Parents' Weekend. Photo 001

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Parents' Weekend. 'Are You Ready, My Sister?' Presented by Underground Railway Theatre. A dramatic performance depicting the historical adventure of Underground Railroad conductor Harriet Tubman and the Quaker women who helped her bring 300 fugitives to freedom. Production by two actresses/puppeteers features dramatic scenes and live music based on the spirituals of the slave era. Recommended for all ages. In Tisch Library room 304.
